         <abstract>
            <p>Families of methods depending on free parameters are constructed for the solution of nonsingular Volterra integral equations of the first kind in [5]. These parameters are restricted to certain regions in order that a certain polynomial satisfies both a stability and a consistency condition. In this note an optimal choice of the free parameters is outlined in order that the $l_2$-norm of the roots of the polynomial is minimized.</p>
          </abstract>
